CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads:"Young Set Have Fun Too At Alpha Dance - Between Sets - The Student Union of the University of Pittsburgh was the scene of youthful gaiety when Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity sponsored a benefit dance for the United Negro College Fund. It was under the supervision of the UNCF's Women's Division, headed by Miss Nancy Lee.  Between dance sets this group got together for a friendly chat.  in group are: JoAnn Griffin, Eric Dykes, Vincent Price, Janene Walker, Darnell Palmer, Francine Foster, Barbara Easley, Deborah Davis, Nathaniel Sims, Deborah Banks and Brenda Price."
TitMainTitle: Seven women and four men, including: JoAnn Griffin, Eric Dykes, Vincent Price, Janene Walker, Darnell Palmer, Francine Foster, Barbara Easley, Deborah Davis, Nathaniel Sims, Deborah Banks, and Brenda Price, gathered on chairs and ottoman in University of Pittsburgh Student Union for Alpha Phi Alpha benefit dance for United Negro College Fund
